      <hedline>
        <hl1>Your Kids Are Their Problem</hl1>
      </hedline>
      <abstract>
        <p>Paul Ruschmann letter on Lisa Belkin's July 23 article on backlash against children holds political ads relegate childless voters to margins of political process</p>
      </abstract>
    </body.head>
    <body.content>
      <block class="lead_paragraph">
        <p>Belkin alluded to the relegation of childless voters to the margins of the political process. On every issue from tax reform to gun control, political ads are filled with touchy-feely slogans and pictures that pander to parents. This sends a strong message to childless voters: we don't want you. Is it any wonder that younger Americans, many of whom haven't yet started families, are increasingly staying away from the polls?</p>
        <p>Paul Ruschmann  Canton, Mich.</p>
      </block>
